narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned how to play famous Gamelan musical instruments, and I learned more about the culture of music in Indonesia.
Developed an understanding and interest in gamelan music; was able to develop my singing skills and teamwork by working with the whole ensemble of instruments
Gamelan Ensemble teaches you about the awesome tradition of Javanese music.
This was an awesome class and I learned a lot about the Gamelan orchestra and how to play the instruments.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Nothing that I can think of - this class was great!
strengths - manageable workload, extremely enthusiastic and knowledgeable teaching staff, seminar style was very conducive to rehearsal needs
The quality of the performance definitely depends on the engagement of other students, so it would be good to mix in a few more musically experienced students if possible!
Great class, doesn't need to be improved, but it would be cool to have another semester of it (like a second part).

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, this class was GREAT. I loved the course a lot, and I learned a lot.
Absolutely recommend Gamelan, if you can get in. It will be a shining light in anyone's semester.
Yes I would recommend this class to any student because I don't have a lot of experience with music but I still loved it and was able to learn how to play. It was so fun and interesting!
Yes! This is a great class and the professor is so sweet.
